In [21]:
def read_nifti_file(filepath):
    """Read and load volume"""
    # Read file
    scan = nib.load(filepath)
    # Get raw data
    scan = scan.get_fdata()
    return scan

def crop(f_data):#79->r(w),95->c(h),79->indx
    """cropping"""
    # Select the ROI
    start_row = 5
    end_row = 74
    start_col = 10
    end_col = 88
    slice_idx = 50
    roi = f_data[start_row:end_row, start_col:end_col, slice_idx]
    return roi

    
def normalize(f_data):
    """Normalize the volume"""
    mean_intensity=np.mean(f_data)
    std_dev=np.std(f_data)
    # Normalize the image using the z-score formula
    normalized_image = (f_data - mean_intensity) / std_dev
    return normalized_image

def resize_volume(f_data):#79->d,95->w,79->h
    """Resize across z-axis"""
    # Get current depth
    current_depth = f_data.shape[-1]
    current_width = f_data.shape[0]
    current_height = f_data.shape[1]
    aspect_ratio = current_width / current_height

    # Choose the new dimensions
    new_height =35
    aspect_ratio=current_width/current_height
    new_width = int(new_height * aspect_ratio)

    # Resize the image using the aspect ratio
    resized_image = np.resize(f_data, (new_height, new_width, f_data.shape[-1]))#f_data.shape[-1]))
    return resized_image


def process_scan(path):
    """Read and resize volume"""
    # Read scan
    volume = read_nifti_file(path)
    roi=crop(volume)
    # Resize width, height and depth
    volume = resize_volume(volume)
    # Normalize
    volume = normalize(volume)
    return volume

import imgaug as ia
import imgaug.augmenters as iaa

def augment_data(data, labels,multiplier):
    """Augment the data and labels using image augmentation techniques"""
    # Define the augmentations to use
    augmentations = iaa.Sequential([
        iaa.Affine(
            rotate=(random.randint(-30,30), random.randint(-30,30)),
            translate_percent={"x": (-0.1, 0.1), "y": (-0.1, 0.1)},
            mode="reflect"
        ),
        iaa.Fliplr(0.5), # Flip horizontally with 50% probability
        iaa.Flipud(0.5),
        #iaa.AdditiveGaussianNoise(scale=(0, 0.1 * 255)),
        #iaa.Multiply((0.8, 1.2), per_channel=0.2),
        iaa.ContrastNormalization((0.5, 1.2))
    ])
    
    # Augment the data and labels
    data_aug = augmentations.augment_images(data)
    labels_aug = labels.repeat(data_aug.shape[0] // labels.shape[0], axis=0)
    
    while data_aug.shape[0] < data.shape[0] * multiplier:
        data_aug_new, labels_aug_new = augment_data(data, labels, multiplier=1)
        data_aug = np.concatenate([data_aug, data_aug_new])
        labels_aug = np.concatenate([labels_aug, labels_aug_new])
    
    return data_aug[:data.shape[0] * multiplier], labels_aug[:data.shape[0] * multiplier]
    
    return data_aug, labels_aug

from tensorflow.keras import regularizers

model=tf.keras.Sequential()

model.add(layers.Conv3D(12, (3, 3, 3), activation='relu',padding='same'))
model.add(layers.MaxPool3D((2, 2, 2)))
model.add(layers.BatchNormalization())

model.add(layers.Conv3D(14, (3, 3, 3), activation='relu',padding='same'))
model.add(layers.MaxPool3D((2, 2, 2)))
model.add(layers.BatchNormalization())

model.add(layers.Flatten())
model.add(layers.Dense(2800, activation='relu',
          kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.02),
                                       bias_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.02)))
model.add(layers.Dropout(0.2))
model.add(layers.Dense(800, activation='relu'))

model.add(layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))

model.build(input_shape=(None, 35, 29, 79, 1)) #l2 0.01 test accurcacy 62%
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])

def create_cm(y1,y2,model):
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(9,5))
    matrix=confusion_matrix(y1,y2)
    labels_cm=['True Negative','False Positive', 'False Negative', 'True Positive']
    samples_count = [str(value) + ' labels' for value in matrix.flatten()]
    metric_per = [str(round(value,2)) for value in matrix.flatten()/np.sum(matrix)]
    labels = [f'{v1}\n\n{v2}\n\n{v3}' for v1, v2, v3 in zip(labels_cm,samples_count ,metric_per)]
    labels = np.asarray(labels).reshape(2,2)
    sns_fig=sns.heatmap(matrix, annot=labels, fmt='', cmap='Blues').set_title('Confusion matrix for '+
                                                                              str(model))
    sns_fig=sns_fig.get_figure()
    return sns_fig.savefig('confusion matrix '+str(model)+'.png',dpi=300)

Non-Sequential model¶

In [37]:
input_shape = (35, 29, 79, 1)

#input layer
input_layer = layers.Input(shape=input_shape)

# wide part
wide_part = layers.Conv3D(14, (3, 3, 3), activation='relu')(input_layer)
wide_part = layers.MaxPool3D((2, 2, 2))(wide_part)
wide_part = layers.Flatten()(wide_part)

# deep part
deep_part = layers.Conv3D(20, (3, 3, 3), activation='relu')(input_layer)
deep_part = layers.MaxPool3D((2, 2, 2))(deep_part)
deep_part = layers.Flatten()(deep_part)
deep_part = layers.Dense(2000, activation='relu',
                         kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.02),
                                bias_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.02))(deep_part)
deep_part = layers.Dropout(0.2)(deep_part)
deep_part = layers.Dense(800, activation='relu')(deep_part)

# Concatenating
concatenated = layers.concatenate([wide_part, deep_part])
output_layer = layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(concatenated)

# model definition
model = tf.keras.Model(inputs=input_layer, outputs=output_layer)
model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Print the model summary
model.summary()

Resnet with one residual block¶

In [37]:
def conv3d(input_tensor, filters, kernel_size, strides, padding):
    return layers.Conv3D(filters=filters,kernel_size=kernel_size,strides=strides,
                         padding=padding)(input_tensor)


def residual_block(input_tensor, filters, kernel_size, strides):
    x = conv3d(input_tensor, filters, kernel_size, strides, padding='same')
    x = layers.BatchNormalization()(x)
    x = layers.ReLU()(x)
    x = layers.Add()([x, input_tensor])
    x = layers.ReLU()(x)
    return x

input_tensor = layers.Input(shape=(35, 29, 79,1))

x = conv3d(input_tensor, 22, 3, 1, padding='same')
x = layers.BatchNormalization()(x)
x = layers.ReLU()(x)

x = residual_block(x, 22, 3, 1)
x = layers.MaxPool3D()(x)

x=layers.Flatten()(x)
x=layers.Dense(1800, activation='relu',kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.02),
                                      bias_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.02))(x)
x=layers.Dropout(0.2)(x)

x=layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

model = tf.keras.Model(input_tensor, x)
optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam()

model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['accuracy'])
model.summary()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Create a figure with two subplots
fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(10,5))

# Plot the histogram of the normal MRI scans
for i in normal_mri_scans_pth:
    img = nib.load(i)
    f_data = img.get_fdata()
    intensities = f_data.flatten()
    ax1.hist(intensities)
    ax1.set_xlabel("Intensity")
    ax1.set_ylabel("Frequency")
    ax1.set_title("Normal MRI Scans")


# Plot the histogram of the abnormal MRI scans
for i in abnormal_mri_scans_pth:
    img1 = nib.load(i)
    f_data1=img1.get_fdata()
    intensities1= f_data1.flatten()
    ax2.hist(intensities1)
    ax2.set_xlabel("Intensity")
    ax2.set_ylabel("Frequency")
    ax2.set_title("Abnormal MRI Scans")
fig.savefig("histograms.png",dpi=300)
plt.show()
